observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to direct the:

Municipal Accountant to prepare the Disbursement Voucher on the reversion of the unexpended balance of LDRRMF-STF from CY 2018 amounting to ₱0.715 million to the General Fund;

Municipal Treasurer to issue a check for the transfer of the unexpended balance of LDRRMF-STF from CY 2018 amounting to ₱0.715 million from LDRRMF-STF account to the General Fund account;

Municipal Accountant to issue a Journal Entry Voucher adjusting the balance of the Trust Liability-DRRM account corresponding to the unexpended balance of LDRRMF-STF from CY 2018 amounting to ₱0.715 million transferred to the General Fund;

Municipal Accountant to prepare a Journal Entry Voucher to reverse the entry made in taking up the DRRM Capital Outlay PPAs as Trust Liability-DRRM in the GF books; and

Municipal Accountant and MDRRMO-Designate to communicate with the source agencies regarding the MOA or any provisions as to the utilization and liquidation of the cash donations received.

We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to direct the GAD Focal Person and other concerned municipal officials and employees to:

Submit the duly reviewed and DILG-endorsed GAD Plan and Budget (GPB) to the Audit Team and follow strictly the provision of PCW-DILG-DBM-NEDA JMC No. 2013-01;

Prepare a timeline for the implementation of the GAD PPAs, taking into consideration the procurement process;

Make proper coordination with the participants before the training/seminar to avoid wastage of government funds; and

Ensure the full implementation of GAD PPAs identified, utilize the allocated budget for GAD to maximize the funds and ensure that the relevant GAD PPAs will address/respond to the gender-related issues identified in the Municipality.

We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to direct the:

Municipal Treasurer to communicate with the PTO and BLGF regarding the setting of Revenue Performance Targets of the Municipality;

Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Assessor to update the records, including the current addresses of land owners in the Municipality to facilitate the sending of Notices of Delinquency;

Municipal Treasurer to follow up on the review and approval of the Municipal Revenue Code by the BLGF from time to time to fast-track its implementation; and

Municipal Treasurer to strictly enforce the collection of the delinquent real property taxes by conducting a more aggressive tax campaign and by implementing the remedies provided for in R.A. No. 7160.

We also recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to communicate with the Province of Iloilo on the status of contested barangays within the Municipality that are adjacent to the Province of Capiz.

We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to instruct the:

Municipal Treasurer to prepare a Schedule of Unreleased Checks as at year-end and provide the same to the Municipal Accountant;

Municipal Accountant to issue a Journal Entry Voucher (JEV) reverting the unreleased checks as at year-end to the Cash in Bank- Local Currency, Current Account based on the schedule provided by the Municipal Treasurer;

Municipal Accountant to adjust the Cash in Bank-Local Currency, Current Account and the corresponding liability/payable accounts reported in the financial statements; and

Municipal Treasurer to ensure that checks are released to the payees by indicating the actual date of receipt in the Check Register and Disbursement Vouchers.

We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to direct the:

Municipal Planning and Development Office to ensure that the development projects funded under the 20% Development Fund are well-planned, procurement- and- implementation ready and properly coordinated with the concerned offices within the Municipality’s jurisdiction to avoid conflict in the implementation;

Municipal Planning and Development Office and Municipal Engineering Office to ensure that the 20% Development Fund be optimally utilized by timely implementing the various programs, projects and activities included in the AIP to help achieve the desirable socio-economic targets and outcomes of the Municipality for the benefit of its constituents;

Municipal Engineer to monitor the project of the Municipality and observe the procedures provided under Item 9, Annex E of the Revised IRR of R.A. No. 9184, in the suspension of work due to justifiable circumstance provided thereto; and 

Municipal Engineer to prepare the PERT/CPM Network Diagram and the Statement of Time-elapsed, as supporting documents to the progress billings.

We recommended and the Management agreed that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Treasurer to strictly enforce the collection of the delinquent market stall rentals by imposing the sanctions provided in the Contract of Lease;

We also recommended and the Management agreed that the Municipal Mayor:

Create a Market Committee to oversee the operations of the public market;

Coordinate with the Sangguniang Bayan to fast-track the update of the Revenue Code; and

Sign the Contract of Lease with the market stall occupants in behalf of the Municipality.

We recommended and the Management agreed that the Municipal Mayor instruct the OIC-Municipal Accountant and HRMO to:

initiate the establishment of policy and guidelines in the selection and recruitment of Job Order and Contract of Service personnel;

specify the duties and functions of each personnel in the Job Order Contract and Contract of Service and make sure that the Job Order personnel conform to the contract by affixing their signature to the contract; 

make sure that the payment of the salaries and wages of Job Order and Contract of Service personnel be supported with the Job Order Contract/Contract of Service and payroll duly signed by the said personnel; and 

indicate in the Accomplishment Report, the quantified and specific duties and functions accomplished during the period.

