We recommended and the Management agreed that the Municipal Mayor instruct the MENRO-Designate and personnel concerned to:

a)	provide assistance to the barangays in the management of their solid wastes and monitor closely the establishment of the Material Recovery Facility in Barangay Dalipe and Layogbato;

b)	refrain from collecting unsegregated wastes from the barangay MRFs and assign laborers to assist in the segregation of wastes in the Residual Containment Area and for final disposal to the sanitary landfill contracted by the Municipality;

c)	intensify the Information Education and Communication campaign on Solid Waste Management and educate the constituents of the waste segregation at source;

d)	initiate the Recycle Activity Training and Composting Technology Training for farmers; and

e)	make use of the shredder and rotary composter and coordinate with the concerned agencies of the possible market for the composted waste.

Recommendations
We reiterated our recommendations and the Municipal Mayor agreed to:
direct the Inventory Committee to prioritize the conduct of the physical count of all PPE and prepare and submit the Report on Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) to the Auditor not later than January 31 of the following year;
require the GSO-Designate and Municipal Accountant to prepare, maintain and update the Property Cards (PC) and PPE Ledger Cards for all PPE accounts; and
direct the Municipal Accountant to submit the complete subsidiary ledgers of all PPE accounts to support the balance recorded in the financial statements;
We further recommended and the Management agreed that the Municipality will avail of the one-time cleansing of PPE accounts as provided under Commission on Audit (COA) Circular No. 2020-006 to finally establish PPE balances that are verifiable as to existence, condition and accountability.

